    <statement><p>Simplify this expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\frac{{\frac{k}{\left(k-6\right)^{2}}}}{{\frac{6k}{k^{2}-36}}}=}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{k+6}{6\mathopen{}\left(k-6\right)}, k\ne 0\hbox{ and }k\ne -6</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simply the complex fraction <m>\frac{{\frac{k}{\left(k-6\right)^{2}}}}{{\frac{6k}{k^{2}-36}}}</m>, we multiple the numerator and denominator with the common denominator of <m>{\frac{k}{\left(k-6\right)^{2}}}</m> and <m>{\frac{6k}{k^{2}-36}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
  \frac{{\frac{k}{\left(k-6\right)^{2}}}}{{\frac{6k}{k^{2}-36}}} \amp = \frac{{\frac{k}{\left(k-6\right)^{2}}}}{{\frac{6k}{\left(k+6\right)\mathopen{}\left(k-6\right)}}} \\
  \amp = \frac{{\frac{k}{\left(k-6\right)^{2}}\mathopen{}\left(k+6\right)\mathopen{}\left(k-6\right)^{2}}}{{\frac{6k}{\left(k+6\right)\mathopen{}\left(k-6\right)}\mathopen{}\left(k+6\right)\mathopen{}\left(k-6\right)^{2}}} \\
  \amp = \frac{{k\mathopen{}\left(k+6\right)}}{{6k\mathopen{}\left(k-6\right)}},k\ne-6 \\
  \amp ={\frac{k+6}{6\mathopen{}\left(k-6\right)}, k\ne 0\hbox{ and }k\ne -6}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factors <m>k</m> and <m>k+6</m> were canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>{k \ne -6\hbox{ and }k \ne 0\hbox{ and }k \ne 6}</m>.</p>
</solution>
